    "name": "John Higgins",
    "profile": "Arranger, Composer, and Producer.\r\nAlso credited as photographer\r\n\r\nHiggins is best known for his many compositions and arrangements for choirs, bands and orchestras. He is currently the Managing Producer/Editor for [l=Hal Leonard Publishing Corporation]. He served as president of [l=Jenson Publications Inc.] before it became a part of the Hal Leonard Corporation He began in the music field as the student arranger for the [a=University of Michigan Band] under Dr. [a=William D. Revelli]. He served as Illinois president of the American String Teachers Association, and as a public school teacher, his school concerts featured renowned soloists and conductors such as [a=Skitch Henderson], [a=Charlie Byrd], and [a=Arthur Fiedler]. \r\n\r\nAs a composer of children's songs, he has collaborated with notables like  John Jacobson, [a=Roger Emerson] and [a=Emily Crocker] on musicals such as [i]How Does Your Garden Grow?[/i] and [i]A Storybook Christmas[/i]. He has also arranged and produced a large c",
